# kube-state-metrics

Generates Prometheus metrics from Kubernetes object state.

- **Namespace**: `openshift-monitoring`
- **Kind**: Deployment (1 replica)
- **Upstream**: [kubernetes/kube-state-metrics](https://github.com/kubernetes/kube-state-metrics)
- **Downstream**: [openshift/kube-state-metrics](https://github.com/openshift/kube-state-metrics)
- **Jsonnet**: `jsonnet/components/kube-state-metrics.libsonnet`

## Key Metric Families

- `kube_pod_*` — Pod status, phase, conditions, restarts, resource requests/limits
- `kube_deployment_*` — Deployment replicas, conditions
- `kube_statefulset_*` — StatefulSet replicas
- `kube_daemonset_*` — DaemonSet counts
- `kube_node_*` — Node conditions, capacity
- `kube_persistentvolumeclaim_*` — PVC status

## Companion

`openshift-state-metrics` — Generates metrics for OpenShift-specific resources (ClusterOperator, Route, Build, etc.). Separate Deployment in `openshift-monitoring`.
